100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 17, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on disarmament and international peace efforts amid rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the ongoing debate surrounding Prohibition intensified, with reports of increasing organized crime linked to illegal liquor. Meanwhile, in India, Mahatma Gandhi continued to gain momentum in his campaign for independence, rallying support against British colonial rule.
